The Situation Room
Live from Washington
Monday, April 9, 2007

IN POLITICS:
•	Pres. Bush Re-launches Push for Immigration Overhaul with Arizona Visit
•	New York Moves its Presidential Primary to February 5

IN THE NEWS:
•	Thousands Gather in Najaf for Anti-American Rally on Major Anniversary
•	Iran: We've Reached “Industrial Level” Nuclear Production
•	Gas Prices on the Rise.  Up More Than 18-cents in Past 2 Weeks: Survey

IN THE CAFFERTY FILE:
•	How much does it matter to you if a presidential candidate has military experience?
•	When it comes to getting the real story about Iraq, whom do you trust more: the media or the military?
•	When it comes to immigration reform, will President Bush have better luck this time around with the Democratic Congress?

